cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about person re-identification using a novel network architecture that factorises the visual appearance of a person into latent discriminative factors at multiple semantic levels without manual annotation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep learning model, which is a key component of the proposed architecture, and achieves state-of-the-art results on three Re-ID datasets. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves modelling discriminative and view-invariant factors of person appearance, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
